        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Sanford</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-07-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 16, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir:</hi> I thank you for your note of the 27th of
                    June. I think M. Thiers is right. Our enemies in Europe want us divided, and
                    thus destroyed. They will not by intervention drive us into closer union and
                    increased vigor.</p>
                <p>I am, my dear sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry S. Sanford</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Brussels.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
